HEADWORD: Aruspex
<hw>A*rus"pex</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Aruspices</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>aruspex</ets>
or <ets>haruspex</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of the class of diviners among
the Etruscans and Romans, who foretold events by the inspection of the
entrails of victims offered on the altars of the gods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

